# Comment preservation (Orbit Wars)

Adapted from [cursorrules-collection `code-quality/preserve-comments.mdc`](https://github.com/nedcodes-ok/cursorrules-collection/blob/main/rules-mdc/code-quality/preserve-comments.mdc).

## Always keep

- **Why** comments (business logic, invariants, non-obvious behavior) — especially in `src/jax/` (shape constraints, scan carry layout, metric merge timing).
- **JAX / rollout notes**: `_merge_metric_dicts` inside `jax.lax.scan`, finalize rates after scan, `pure_callback` boundaries, feature-history vs `opp_batch_cache`.
- **Hydra/runtime mismatches**: when YAML defaults differ from `src/config/schema.py`.
- **Ticket / review references**: GitHub issue/PR ids, dated deprecations, “do not modify” guards.
- **Import-layer constraints** from `docs/architecture/README.md`.

## Orbit Wars–specific

- Do not delete comments that document **TurnBatch** dims, `edge_k(task)`, or pointer-decoder modes — agents often “clean up” these during refactors.
- Preserve step-by-step flow comments in long training/rollout functions unless the code moved and the comment is updated to match.

## OK to remove

- Demonstrably wrong (contradicted by current code).
- Exact duplicate in the same file.
- Meaningless auto-generated boilerplate.

When in doubt, **keep** the comment. Prefer updating stale comments over deleting them.
